<paragraph id="8B8AB037FFEEFFC97787F8AD1B3C517C" blockId="20.[151,764,1846,1973]" lastBlockId="20.[809,1422,178,1313]" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">
Three individuals of this large orange-colored bat were captured at FC, all in the canopy net set over the creek. These were initially identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC97270FF661D5254B0" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97270FF661D5254B0" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using the keys by Hayman and Hill (1971) but following 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC9749BFF211A685552" author="Robbins" box="[929,1112,245,271]" firstAuthor="Robbins" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" pagination="212 - 213" refId="ref19327" refString="ROBBINS, C. B. 1978. Taxonomic identification and history of Scotophilus nigrita (Schreber) (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae). Journal of Mammalogy, 59: 212 - 213." type="journal article" year="1978">Robbins (1978)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC973B5FF211BB85552" author="Robbins" box="[1167,1416,245,271]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Robbins" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" pagination="51 - 84" refId="ref19361" refString="ROBBINS, C. B., F. DE VREE, and V. VAN CAKENBERGHE. 1985. A systematic revision of the African bat genus Scotophilus (Vespertilionidae). Zoologische Wetenschappen, 246: 51 - 84." type="journal article" year="1985">
Robbins 
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC973CDFF211B015552" box="[1271,1329,245,271]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">et al.</emphasis>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC97413FEC21D95556D" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[809,933,278,304]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97413FEC21D95556D" box="[809,933,278,304]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should now be considered a senior synonym of the much larger 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC97341FEEC1AE8550F" box="[1147,1240,312,338]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97341FEEC1AE8550F" box="[1147,1240,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED2428F2FFEEFFC973DCFEEC1B3A550F" box="[1254,1290,312,338]" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">FA</collectionCode>
= 
<quantity id="4CCD1DD2FFEEFFC97210FEEC1B4E550F" box="[1322,1406,312,338]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.6" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" unit="mm" value="86.0">86 mm</quantity>
). The smaller 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC97480FE8E1A735529" box="[954,1091,346,372]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97480FE8E1A735529" box="[954,1091,346,372]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">Scotophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode id="ED2428F2FFEEFFC9736AFE8E1A445529" box="[1104,1140,346,372]" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">FA</collectionCode>
= 
<quantity id="4CCD1DD2FFEEFFC973A8FE8E1B235529" box="[1170,1299,346,372]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="5.9" metricValueMin="5.1" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" unit="mm" value="55.0" valueMax="59.0" valueMin="51.0">51–59 mm</quantity>
), formerly called 
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC9744FFEAF1DD955C8" box="[885,1001,379,405]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC9744FFEAF1DD555C8" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[885,997,379,405]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">S. nigrita</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
are now either 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC973A6FEAF1B2A55C8" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1180,1306,379,405]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dinganii">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC973A6FEAF1B2A55C8" box="[1180,1306,379,405]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. dinganii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC97205FEAF1BB555C8" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[1343,1413,379,405]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nux">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97205FEAF1BB555C8" box="[1343,1413,379,405]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. nux</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Similarly, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC97489FE491B2555EA" author="Konstantinov" box="[947,1301,413,439]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Konstantinov" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" pagination="129 - 148" refId="ref18332" refString="KONSTANTINOV, O. K., A. I. PEMA, V. V. L ABZIN, and G. V. FARA- FONOVA. 2000. Records of bats from Middle Guinea, with remarks on their natural history. Plecotus et al., 3: 129 - 148." type="journal article" year="2000">
Konstantinov 
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97350FE491A8255EA" box="[1130,1202,413,439]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">et al.</emphasis>
(2000)
</bibRefCitation>
reported a specimen ‘near Kindia’ as 
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC973B6FE6B1B355584" box="[1164,1285,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC973B6FE6B1B315584" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1164,1281,447,473]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">S. nigrita</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but Weber and Fahr (2007 
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC974E1FE341DDA55A7" box="[987,1002,480,506]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">b</emphasis>
) correctly pointed out that based on the forearm measurement (
<quantity id="4CCD1DD2FFEEFFC97359FDD61A885641" box="[1123,1208,514,540]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" unit="mm" value="51.0">51 mm</quantity>
) the identification of this specimen needs to be either 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC973DFFDF71B595660" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1253,1385,547,573]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dinganii">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC973DFFDF71B595660" box="[1253,1385,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. dinganii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC97413FD911D405602" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[809,880,581,607]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nux">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97413FD911D405602" box="[809,880,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. nux</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The identification as 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC9734EFD911A8B5602" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[1140,1211,581,607]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nux">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC9734EFD911A8B5602" box="[1140,1211,581,607]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. nux</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was confirmed in a molecular genetic study that included our voucher specimen from FC (
<collectionCode id="ED2428F2FFEEFFC97324FD5C1A0556FF" box="[1054,1077,648,674]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">R</collectionCode>
. G. Trujillo, in litt.). During the 2003 RAP, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC974DAFD7E1A835699" author="Fahr" box="[992,1203,682,708]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Fahr" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" pagination="168 - 180" refId="ref17134" refString="FAHR, J., B. A. DJOSSA, and H. VIERHAUS. 2006. Rapid assessment of bats (Chiroptera) in the Dere, Diecke and Mt. Bero classified forests, Southeastern Guinea; including a review of the distribution of bats in Guinee Forestiere. Pp. 168 - 180, in A rapid biological assessment of three classified forests in southeastern Guinea (H. E. WRIGHT, J. MC- CULLOUGH, L. E. ALONSO, and M. S. DIALLO, eds.). RAP Bulletin of Biological Assessment 40. Conservation International, Washington, D. C., 248 pp." type="book chapter" year="2006">
Fahr 
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97325FD7E1A6C5699" box="[1055,1116,682,708]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
caught one specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC974AAFD181DEE56BB" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[912,990,716,742]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nux">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC974AAFD181DEE56BB" box="[912,990,716,742]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. nux</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Kpinita (Kpogo River), Mount Béro, and they refer to another specimen from the Forêt Classée de Diecké mentioned in Bützler (1994). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC974BCFCE51A215716" author="Fahr" box="[902,1041,817,843]" firstAuthor="Fahr" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" refId="ref16603" refString="FAHR, J. 1996. Die Chiroptera der Elfenbeinkuste (unter Berucksichtigung des westafrikanischen Raumes): Taxonomie, Habitatpraferenzen und Lebensgemeinschaften. Diploma Thesis, Julius-Maximilians-Universitat, Wurzburg, 204 pp. + 36 maps." type="book" year="1996">Fahr (1996)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC973E2FCE51B6B5716" author="Hill" box="[1240,1371,817,843]" firstAuthor="Hill" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" pagination="116 - 120" refId="ref17917" refString="HILL, J. E. 1982. Records of bats from Mount Nimba, Liberia. Mammalia, 46: 116 - 120." type="journal article" year="1982">Hill (1982)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC97413FC861A165731" author="Wolton" box="[809,1062,850,876]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Wolton" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" pagination="419 - 448" refId="ref20510" refString="WOLTON, R. J., P. A. ARAK, H. C. J. GODFRAY, and R. P. WILSON. 1982. Ecological and behavioral studies of the Megachiroptera at Mount Nimba, Liberia, with notes on Microchiroptera. Mammalia, 46: 419 - 448." type="journal article" year="1982">
Wolton 
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC974B1FC861DFB5731" box="[907,971,850,876]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">et al.</emphasis>
(1982)
</bibRefCitation>
list two specimens from the Liberian portion of Mount Nimba under 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC97237FCA01BBD57D3" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1293,1421,884,910]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dinganii">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97237FCA01BBD57D3" box="[1293,1421,884,910]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. dinganii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but found that forearm measurements by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC97230FC411BBD57F2" author="Hill" box="[1290,1421,917,943]" firstAuthor="Hill" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" pagination="116 - 120" refId="ref17917" refString="HILL, J. E. 1982. Records of bats from Mount Nimba, Liberia. Mammalia, 46: 116 - 120." type="journal article" year="1982">Hill (1982)</bibRefCitation>
are clearly above the range for this species so that these specimens should also be assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC97201FC0D1BB557AE" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[1339,1413,985,1011]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nux">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97201FC0D1BB557AE" box="[1339,1413,985,1011]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. nux</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Most occurrences of 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC97301FC2E1ABB5049" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[1083,1163,1018,1044]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nux">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97301FC2E1ABB5049" box="[1083,1163,1018,1044]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. nux</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are associated with the high forest zone from 
<collectingCountry id="F322F0A7FFEEFFC97351FBC81B35506B" box="[1131,1285,1052,1078]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
to western 
<collectingCountry id="F322F0A7FFEEFFC97413FBEA1D465005" box="[809,886,1086,1112]" name="Kenya" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC974BDFBEA1AB45005" author="Robbins" box="[903,1156,1086,1112]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Robbins" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" pagination="51 - 84" refId="ref19361" refString="ROBBINS, C. B., F. DE VREE, and V. VAN CAKENBERGHE. 1985. A systematic revision of the African bat genus Scotophilus (Vespertilionidae). Zoologische Wetenschappen, 246: 51 - 84." type="journal article" year="1985">
Robbins 
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC974CFFBEA1A035005" box="[1013,1075,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">et al.</emphasis>
, 1985
</bibRefCitation>
). At Nimba it reaches 
<quantity id="4CCD1DD2FFEEFFC97413FB8B1D455024" box="[809,885,1119,1145]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" unit="m" value="600.0">600 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC974BCFB8B1A345024" author="Hill" box="[902,1028,1119,1145]" firstAuthor="Hill" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" pagination="116 - 120" refId="ref17917" refString="HILL, J. E. 1982. Records of bats from Mount Nimba, Liberia. Mammalia, 46: 116 - 120." type="journal article" year="1982">Hill, 1982</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC97320FB8B1B005024" author="Grubb" box="[1050,1328,1119,1145]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Grubb" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" refId="ref17443" refString="GRUBB, P., T. S. JONES, A. G. DAVIES, E. EDBERG, E. D. STARIN, and J. E. HILL. 1998. Mammals of Ghana, Sierra Leone and the Gambia. The Trendrine Press, Cornwall, 265 pp." type="book" year="1998">
Grubb 
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97354FB8B1A9A5024" box="[1134,1194,1119,1145]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">et al.</emphasis>
(1998: 91)
</bibRefCitation>
discuss this species as the “forest form” of 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC973F2FB551B7850C6" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1224,1352,1153,1179]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dinganii">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC973F2FB551B7850C6" box="[1224,1352,1153,1179]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">S. dinganii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97263FB551D6350E1" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">
S. d. 
<taxonomicName id="4C35CBB4FFEEFFC97413FB761D6350E1" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[809,851,1186,1212]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nux">nux</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) and report that 
<collectionCode id="ED2428F2FFEEFFC97323FB761A1C50E1" box="[1049,1068,1186,1212]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">T</collectionCode>
. J. Jones “found it quite common in built up areas where it roosted in small groups in the roofs of houses and thatched huts” and “it has also been taken in holes in trees.”
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32FE3BCFFEEFFC97413FA9F1DE651F5" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8B8AB037FFEEFFC97413FA9F1A235138" blockId="20.[809,1421,1355,1448]" box="[809,1043,1355,1381]" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis id="B9416C25FFEEFFC97413FA9F1A235138" box="[809,1043,1355,1381]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">Conservation status</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8AB037FFEEFFC97475FAB81DE651F5" blockId="20.[809,1421,1355,1448]" pageId="20" pageNumber="274">
Least Concern. Population trend unknown (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA4CDC6FFEEFFC9740BFA5A1DFA51F5" author="IUCN" box="[817,970,1422,1448]" firstAuthor="IUCN" pageId="20" pageNumber="274" refId="ref18094" refString="IUCN 2015. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2014.1. Available at http: // www. iucnredlist. org. Downloaded on 12 June 2015." type="url" year="2015">IUCN, 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
